content.detailedDescription: Walked outside to walk dog.  notice triangle shape in sky. not moving like other aircraft.  was about 10:30 pm.  called sons out to verify what i was seeing and let me know color of lights as yellowish orange as i'm colorblind.  walked toward direction to find a clearing to observe.  triangle lights broke apart and disappeared. could not locate in sky in any other clearing.  returned home and triangle lights appeared again
content.summary: Triangle shaped object stationary to slight flutter movement

content.detailedDescription: During the afternoon i was driving with my cousin on i-405 south, through west los angeles, and saw an extremely bright light in the sky, which i first thought was the reflection of a plane going by. it didn't appear to be moving, but sometimes planes don't either, depending on the angle form which you're viewing. it suddenly disappeared, which i thought was strange, given the clear conditions outside. about 10 seconds later it reappeared at the same spot, with the same intensity of light that it had before. it disappeared less than a minute later, and, i thought it reappeared in a slightly different spot (a little higher and to the left), but it was a separate one. the original became visible again, so now there were 2. again, less than a minute later, they vanished (i am not sure at the same time or at different times, i looked away), and reappeared about 10 seconds later, but the one that was at the top left was now at the bottom right of the original. they remained in that position for no more than 30 more seconds before disappearing for the last time. the biggest reason i believe they are not air planes is that the airplanes that were in the sky before, and very soon after, were completely dark. there was no sun shining extremely brought off of the metal of the plane, and there was no plane that even resembled a giant ball of light, especially at this time of the day. also, they were hovering.
content.summary: Extremely bright objects in the sky near lax

content.detailedDescription: On november 12, 2016 at approximately 6:00pm i went out on my balcony and noticed what looked like star off in the distance sky. i quickly realized it was too large to be a star so i assumed it must be an airplane. it appeared not to be moving at all so i assumed it must be headed directly my direction lights pointed this way. i continued to watch for the next 15 minutes bewildered since it never got closer, just hovered in place. took great pics. called my nephew to make sure i wasn't dreaming and he took additional pics from his place. the object/ light/ drone? didn't move an inch for over an hour. i'm attaching the pis here.
content.summary: Noticed what looked like a oversized star. thought it may be aircraft but no movement for 1 to 2 hours. took pics, called nephew, he took pics too.

content.detailedDescription: Sunday, approx. 12 noon (est), sunny skies, few light clouds. i let my dog out and stood in the front yard with him. nice day, looking above the trees at the blue sky. noticed several white dots to the north, growing larger, approaching my position more or less. geese was my first thought. dots grew larger, solid white, in a line, so not geese. no wings, just white. four, maybe five bright white dots in a staggered line, fairly low to my horizon (looking up a hillside). all disappeared for about 10-20 seconds behind a nearby tree as i moved to a better position to see. a bright white egg-shaped light passed beyond the tree to the northwest, flashing like a plane less than a mile off (unless it was huge). now i'm thinking of davison army airfield a few miles away. then a second and third object followed a few seconds later, these also bright white, but not flashing like the first. the sun was above and behind the objects, so they were not reflecting but seemed to generate their own light. there was no sound. i saw no sign of the one or two more dots i'd originally seen, but while watching for them i noticed a commercial jet with contrails emerging into the same field of view. also, i could hear the jet. for comparison, both the objects and the jet seemed to be moving at the same speed, but the jet seemed to be at a much higher altitude. as far as i could tell, these were not meteors, birds, or aircraft from the army airfield, nor commercial traffic. wish i'd had my camera or cell phone with me. 24 hours later, i'm already doubting myself about what i'd seen.
content.summary: 5 lights approach, 3 pass nearby, midday

content.detailedDescription: Super beings called troy. iq around 3000. lifespan around 1000years. they are telepaths. they are androgynous. they are female. in a ship in a stationary orbit around 800 miles from earth. their work is to control humans on earth. they have very advanced technology - around 1,000,000 years beyond earth technology. of the several human civilizations in the universe, we here on earth, i'm guessing, are the least advanced. there are 150 - 200 civilizations in the universe. the population of the universe is, give or take, around 1 trillion intelligent beings. they, troy, have been doing what they do to me for over 26 years now. i am quite tired and worn out from trying to expose them for over 20 years now. i thought exposing them might motivate them to leave me alone - it did'nt!
content.summary: Ship is 3/4 mile in diameter, circular, silver metallic

content.detailedDescription: I was in a really deep sleep early hours of sunday morning after spending a couple of days helping my daughter move house,so was totally exhausted & sleeping heavily i think.I suddenly woke up with a start by a bright light that was flashing through my bedroom & going on & off,this light was a reddish/pink colour to start with but then it became a kind of white light flashing on & off.I sat up in bed with my heart racing as i was quite scared,the light seemed to be coming from outside my bedroom window i would say it was kind of pulsating on & off very frequently.I was quite annoyed as i was so tired & wanted to sleep,i decided to try to go back to sleep so lay back down pulling the duvet over my head.The light was still in my face however & i sat up & turned on the light...By now i was really scared,not sure what to do.I wanted to look out of the window but was scared,i decided to open the curtains & was totally amazed by what i saw...There was a silvery sphere/disc hovering above my back garden & it honestly seemed to be very close to my bedroom window...I am not sure how far away it was about 8feet away or something & only about tree top height i think.It was spinning or pulsating kind of but somehow not moving off of the spot kind of hovering i would say.There were rosy & whitish coloured lights all around the bottom of it that were pulsating & a strong white beam was pointing in my direction.It was silvery/chrome/white coloured & looked seamless i could not see any windows or anything.I was very shocked & afraid but i have seen something similar back in 2012 only that time their were six of them in two rows of three.I was half blinded by the beam of light that was flashing on & off so i may be lacking in some detail of the object & i was terrified.I did not take a picture or video as my camera battery was flat but i felt glued to the spot anyway.I wanted to scream or cry out so that my son in the room next door might come running into my room but when i opened my mouth no sound came out.I am not sure how long i stood there but i know that when i went over to the window it was 4.10am & dark outside,to be honest i am not sure how or when it went away as i woke up in bed at 7.30am,but do not remember going back to bed.I am sure that this was not a dream as i kept on slapping my face & pinching myself to make sure that i was awake.Through all of this i did not hear any sounds at all like an aircraft would make it was just silence,i kept on wishing that i would hear the noise of a helicopter or something as that would then explain it. i do not want this to be a ufo sighting as it terrifies me,because i have had two other sightings in 2001.2012 & this on sunday morning 13/11/16 & that worries me greatly as it feels like i may have been tagged or something.
content.summary: I was in a deep sleep early hours of sunday morning,exhausted after helping my daughter to move house.I was suddenly awoken by strange,flashing reddish/pinkish lighflashing on & off into my bedroom hitting me right in the eyes it seemed to be coming fro

content.detailedDescription:
I would like to share with you a strange event that happened to me ... in 1988 while driving towards the home of my cousin i saw a ufo coming from the north and stopped about 500 meters away over the tennis center, i looked at it and after 3-5 seconds is flying at great speed and disappeared in a split second.
when i arrived at the home of my cousin i told him, "you will not believe what i just saw," he replied, "you have  seen a ufo ... we also see him from here" and he confirmed to me that i didn't  imagined.
the strange in this story is that i discovered just a month ago .... i told the incident to  someone with my wife, then my wife tells me she was in the  car with me ... and i did not remember it for 28 years.
content.summary: Saucer with colorful lights around

content.detailedDescription: I was 13 years old, while sitting in the living room watching tv, i saw a cigar shape with lights encircling it. it came from behind a step hill, i could see the silhouette of the trees in front. momentarily the top of the hill lit up and turned from white to red and disappeared upwards.  i was less than a mile from it.  i yelled for my parents to come but by then it was gone.  my aunt and uncle and cousin said they had witnessed something cigar shape moving over their trailer park with similar lights but only making a hum noise. the lived about a half mile from our home in the country.
content.summary: Sitting in living room watching tv, saw cigar shape with lights over small mt less than a mile away.  quickly disappeared into the air. i saw the trees in front of it as silhouette

content.detailedDescription:
I got off work in sherbrooke at 6:20pm. i started off home and saw a large light in the sky when i got to goldenville, 6:23pm. i pulled over and looked at it for a couple of minutes, taking a photo of it before it disappeared over the horizon. the color of the light seemed to slowly fade in and out between yellow and orange, while maintaining its brightness/size.

i saw it again over a clear cut area in liscomb, just past gegogan brooke, at 6:30
i have seen many odd things in the sky over the years, so i was not afraid.

when i first saw the light appeared to be over the highway, moving towards the right over the horizon. of course, this light was way off in the distance, but was bright. i have no idea how far away it really was or how large.
when i saw it again over the clear cut,moving from left to right in the sky. i pulled over and watched it, took some photos. as i was watching it, the light quickly changed direction and became smaller and smaller as if it was moving quickly away from me. it disappeared completely and was gone for about a minute(?), when it came speeding back to full brightness! there was no cloud cover. i figured at that moment that i better continue on my way down the road. i was not afraid, though a bit uneasy when i saw it come back.
my camera is not high tech, but i was able to get a clear photo of it over the highway, and then again when it was over the clear cut area. i zoomed in best i could for a couple of the photos.
when i got home and zoomed in close on the image, i was surprised to see a "saucer" shape.
although i was alone when i saw this in my car, when i posted this on facebook, a lady from further down the shore said that she also saw this light in mushaboom while traveling to murphys cove.

the next night, november 11th, i saw this light again (or a similar light), only from my living room window. i live in moser river, approximately 45 minutes from where i saw the light the night before.
i was sitting here watching my pet bird, whose cage is by the window, when i noticed the light. i ran outside with my room mate to look at it.
he did not think anything of it, as it was hovering stationary for about 10 minutes until it zoomed out and disappeared out of sight. when it sped off he was a little creeped out. but as usual, i was calm.
as mentioned previously, i have seen a lot of weird things in the sky during my lifetime. this is the first one i am reporting officially due to the fact that the shape came out clear in the photos. most times i never think of getting my camera out, or i don't have time.
content.summary: Large, star like object. when photos brown up looks like sterotypical ufo

content.detailedDescription:
Me and a friend had just left knotts berry farm 1am, we were walking home and took a short cut thru the elematary school my friend stop to relieve himself,i was about 50 feet away from him, i noticed something in the air it was large very large and dark.I looked at my friend he was still urinating but had one hand pointed at this object with his mouth open i looked back quickly in amazement this object moved or stranformed as the bottom lit up with fantastic florescent colors, (the light patterns were beautiful) then the lights got much brighter blinding, i looked at my friend. i am on my bed at home looking out the window from the 2nd floor my hands gripping the window sill, i watched this object take off very fast unbelievably fast. i think i was in shock, i picked up the phone failed my friend his mother picked up i asked for my friend his mother said do you know what time it is, it's 5 in the morning this better be important, i said just get him please, he got on the phone and i asked him dave how did we get home? in a scared voice he said " i don't know, i don't know how we got home, his mother made him hang up. i believe i was abducted that night, nothing can convince me different! it has been many years ago now and not sure if it was 78 or 79 but i had not graduated yet!
i was 16 or 17 when this happened, i called a few people i though may help, told my parents and friends they laughed or brushed it off, as for my friend he has no recolectionon how we arrived home, as for me it has never left my mind. since then i have been interested in knowing about these incidents and i am now 52,i have stopped waiting for them to return and think it time i share my experience. 
sincerely,
kyle walthers
content.summary: Walking home, saw large dark object direcy above me, looked at friend he was pointing. strange large florescent pattern appeared (globe like) next thing i know i am at home with hands on window sill watching this thing fly away, it was now 5am.Mch more hp

content.detailedDescription: I was riding in a car coming back from wilbur hot springs. i was on the freeway, interstate 80, near vacaville. i was talking with a friend who was driving. i looked to my right out the window and saw a large, hovering, purplish blue color saturn-like object in the sky. it was bright, but it was in the distance. it seemed a little transparent and slightly fuzzy. it seemed surreal. in a few seconds, maybe 7, in just disappeared. i never saw it move. it seemed to be at an angle. i never saw anything like this. it was mysterious and a little exciting to see. it was far away. the windows in the car were up. i knew immediately it was a ufo. i told my friend who was driving that i just saw something that looked like a ufo. it was very strange. i can't stop thinking about it. i drew a sketch of it.
content.summary: I saw a bluish-purple, saturn-shaped object in sky. it was hovering, then just disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: I was standing in the backyard looking at the full moon with my wife. she sees a bright green pulsating orb/light moving from west to east and asks if i think it's a plane. there was no noise associated that we could hear. suddenly another orb appears. this one was also moving west to east. it was bright white but also had an odd billowing bulbous shape to it. it was more dull than a star or plane. no faa lights or pulsations. wife ran in the home to grab her mom to witness. after they both came to the yard, the lights both intersected in front of us and slowly both objects came to a stop. we took multiple photos. they remained stationary for a few minutes. as they were stopped, another fast moving bright orb moved from south to north, and passed overhead until it was out of view. green pulsating light slowly starts moving again. goes east. a few mins later, white orb starts moving north, slowly periodically starting and stopping. after a couple mins it turns and starts heading east seemingly following the same path as the green orb just took. after it has moved away from our view due to trees, another bright large white orb appears moving from south to north. it's bigger than the other 3 and intersects with an overhead plane. it steadily moves over the house and stops in the far distance. you can tell it's not moving anymore due to it approaching tree tops but then is still being able to see it for about 3 mins. there was a very dim circular  pulsation being admitted from it. it sat there pulsating softly until it started moving again northward out of sight.Photos are not great as i only has my iphone 5s camera available. but you can see the movement in relation to the silhouettes of the power lines.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: 4 bright orbs moving in a very odd way.

content.detailedDescription: About a week ago we saw this in the night sky ....Thought it was a plane but now a week later still hovering with flashing lights ...But no movement ...Maybe 10k to 15 k in altitude.....Noticed when walking the dogs ....Thought it was a star but twinkled too much...Saw red and green flashes ....Took out binoculars and confirmed erratic red/green and white flashes....No plane or helicopter would hoover that long ...Very perplexing ....If not a plane or helicopter what is it?
content.summary: For the last 4 days hovering in the sky at night with flashing lights red green and white without movement seen with binoculars

content.detailedDescription: Excited to see the supermoon and take pictures, i placed both my celestron (starter) telescope and new dslr camera with tripod on my patio. at approximately 6:50 just after trying unsuccessfully to take good pictures with my dslr (software too smart, i guess), i sat back at the telescope, adjusted it again, and looked through the eyepiece. i was astonished to see a small black circle moving across the moon's surface. it did not do a straight line across it, it did a curved trajectory on the upper part of the moon (from the angle of view) until it reached the other side of the moon and could not longer be seen. i am sure there will be more reports of this as the perfect looking black circle was very distinguishable as it (very quickly) went across.
content.summary: While looking at supermoon with starter telescope, saw black circular object make curved path across moon

content.detailedDescription: I was out at night and noticed a a sparkling light i thought was a star then i observed them with binoculars and could see at least 2 sets of 3 and 4-5 near the patterned lights very obvious they were not planes or stars and there were at least 6-7 planes or helicopters that had flown near the lights through out the night . my wife and son both agreed without hesitation that we were seeing ufos or i would say star ships .  i am an avid believer and have never been sure of seeing ufos until now. my mother and grandmother actually had a sighting in the 50's in downtown baltimore the ship was hovering over a church
content.summary: 3 sparkling sets of lights in a line with one offset and 2 brighter ones on the left and right of the 3

content.detailedDescription: My friend and i were out smoking a cigarette when we noticed two bright orange glowing lights through the trees. one of the lights was higher up in the sky, and after observing them for a while we deemed the lower light to be a plane. then from the garage light behind us we noticed a shadow and we thought it was my friends mom, and she doesn't like us smoking so we got nervous for a second, but it turned out to be a leaf. we then brought our attention back to our cigarettes and conversations when i noticed that the light that was higher up in the sky was still there, but the lower one was not (because it was a plane). we were trying to figure out what it was when all of the sudden it completely vanished into the clouds that were way above it. it was unlike anything either of us have seen before, as it appeared to have been sucked into he clouds. it left no trail, made no noise, did nothing else besides move extremely slowly across the sky. it had orangish-reddish lights being emitted from all apparently spherical parts of the object. we were in complete amazement and were so excited to have seen something we can actually call an unidentified flying object. during our excitement i move my eyes back to where we saw it, and noticed another slow moving object that was exactly identical to the other ufo in every way. moved slowly, glowed, and about 5 seconds later it also vanished into the clouds the same way as the first.
content.summary: Slow moving orange lights appear to get sucked into the clouds with no trail or normal flight pattern

content.detailedDescription:
Was sitting outside my home talking on the phone.  many planes go over my home, presumably on their way into midway/o'hare airports.  i saw a single orange pulsating light traveling on a straight flightpath going from west to east.  i could not see any sort of airframe, and it made no noises.  it altitude was lower than flights that usually go over my home, but its altitude was higher than the medical helicopter that flies over.  it speed was steady and seemed slightly faster than the flights i see going over my home.   i did not see any changes in the flight path or speed the whole time i had the object in sight.  about a minute later, came another orange light on the same flightpath with the same speed.
i was in such disbelief that i did not think to film them with my phone camera and no one else was outside with me at the time.
content.summary: Unknown object with orange pulsating light with another of the same description object two minutes later

content.detailedDescription: Was sitting outside waiting for a friend to come home when i saw this light and i looked up and there was this round spinning object that was covered in lights all around. it was hovering in the same spot for a few minutes until i decided to zoom in on it and then it became more active and dissapeared up into the sky.
content.summary: Was sitting outside and this object just appeared out of nowhere and as i began to zoom in on it, that's when it started to ascend up into the clouds.

content.detailedDescription: Last night i went out onto the patio to have a cigarette. i looked over to the east and noticed a bright light twinkling in the sky. i focused on it and noticed it was very high up and far away. when looking at the orb it  twinkled like a star would except it was much brighter, larger and twinkled blue and white. i decided to record a video on my iphone. i took a video of the orb and then two zoomed in videos to see if i could see details. i saw in the videos the object flashed not only blue and white, but also green. i was outside watching it for about 10 minutes and it didn't move the whole time. it never disappeared as far as i know, i just went back into my house.
content.summary: Flashing stationary orb in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I work at the location of the sighting and was with a young person traveling north by car along redmoor bank in a northerly direction. a bright white light caught my eye and i was very certain that due to the objects brightness and movement that it was not an ordinary aircraft. it grew in brightness and trailed among the clouds, changing direction perhaps 2 times and diminished in brightness gradually before moving behind cloud. the object was not seen again after the cloud had moved. no sound  was heard as i slowed the car to observe and wound the window down. my feeling was one of awe and my hairs on the back of my neck stood on end, i felt like i had expected to see something like this at this time and thought that the sighting was a confirmation or acknowledgement of some kind. the other witness did notice the object visually but said that they paid no attention to it until i pointed at it. sight of the object was lost when it was seen to diminish in brightness by more than 30 times and moved behind cloud in a northerly direction instead of easy to west when it was at its most brightest. noteable areas are: raf wittering and mod n. luffenham. regular military flights take place in the area  with typhoons and eurofighters and their flight patterns are predictable and markedly different. the landing lights on these aircraft are very much dimmer to the light i witnessed.
content.summary: An intense bright white star-like light appeared 40 deg above the horizon and changed direction east to west then west to east before diminishing in intensity and moved behind cloud cover.

content.detailedDescription: I saw a bright white vertical rectangle in the sky. it was waiter glowing or reflecting light. i began recording it once i realized it was actually descending towards earth. i think it may have been hovering at first, but i can't say for sure. i saw it vanish into thin air after a minute. my phone died shortly afterwards even though it was at 17%. i have never seen anything like this in my life. i keep hearing a lot of planes flying in the sky now...Im not sure if this means anything, but i believe that every little detail counts.
content.summary: I saw a bright white vertical rectangle in the sky. i began recording it once i realized it was actually descending towards earth. i think it may have been hovering at first, but i can't say for sure. i saw it vanish into thin air after a minute.

content.detailedDescription:
I was in bed, woke up and looked out back windows. observed an oval shaped series of white lights.The oval was on end as opposed to horizontal. the lights were stationary and unchanged until a red flarelike object was ejected towards 7 o'clock. a yellow light at 1;30 o'clock then came on for a couple of seconds. the lights "zoomed" in towards the house on two occasions with a bright light in the center coming on during one of the zooms. after about 1 hour it moved horizontally from one window frame into another where it remained until gradually disappearing altogether.
there was a"balloon" festival in deming, about 55 miles away in the general direction of the lights. auto dealers sometimes put up a large weather type
balloon for advertising, but did not notice anything in the air when daylight came.

content.detailedDescription: On my way to do groceries, i noticed something in sky, too big & bright to be an airplane.  i parked facing the light in the sky.  i thought, that's not an airplane.  then i noticed a smaller one to the left, both hovering together.  i began filming.  while filming, it looked as though it was getting brighter and changing shape.  i switched to photo and zoomed in.  i said to myself "i think i'm hallucinating."  and clicked a bunch of pics in a row.  i don't know if it's just me, but in the video where the larger light on the right, stops hovering and steers off to the left, it looks to me like it changes from a light to, i don't know what, but it's light starts to look like the flashing lights of an airplane.  the other light hung around for a few min more, but i didn't think to zoom in on it.  i just clicked pics till it just "poof" was no longer there.
content.summary: I thought, that's not an airplane.There's 2.Think it's changing shape.I'm hallucinating looking at pics)
